{"parentUuid":"17508135-c540-4548-850e-f3018cdc9804","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"8cb584c6-6387-4c83-b506-fb1ef5a9a08f","agentId":"a85079ae82257d010","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012XF4pKMnYHcrvfX7F5Keeg","type":"tool_result","content":"143\t# internal = false is INTENTIONAL: this is the public entry point for the\n144\t# Meterly API (an internet-facing ALB is the designed architecture — CLAUDE.md\n145\t# \"ALB\"). \"Load balancer is exposed publicly\" (AWS-0053) is therefore an accepted,\n146\t# by-design property, not a misconfiguration:\n147\t#trivy:ignore:AVD-AWS-0053 Public API — the ALB is internet-facing by design; access is fronted by HTTPS-only ingress, API-key auth, and per-key rate limiting.\n148\tresource \"aws_lb\" \"this\" {\n149\t  name               = \"${var.name_prefix}-alb\"\n150\t  internal           = false\n151\t  load_balancer_type = \"application\"\n152\t  security_groups    = [var.alb_security_group_id]\n153\t  subnets            = var.public_subnet_ids\n154\t\n155\t  # Drop malformed HTTP headers at the edge rather than forwarding them to the\n156\t  # app (defends against header-smuggling; clears AWS-0052).\n157\t  drop_invalid_header_fields = true\n158\t}\n159\t\n160\t# Blue/green target groups — deploy.yml shifts the listener rule's weighted\n161\t# forward action between these during a canary rollout.\n162\tresource \"aws_lb_target_group\" \"blue\" {\n163\t  name        = \"${var.name_prefix}-tg-blue\"\n164\t  port        = 8000"}]},"uuid":"12737c79-af3d-4355-9426-c22a56482ec3","timestamp":"2026-07-10T05:12:26.279Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"17508135-c540-4548-850e-f3018cdc9804","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"ci-fix/required-checks-green"}
